      <acqinfo id="aspace_18329f163821e4a5b7a0c960fbac8316">
         <head>Immediate Source of Acquisition</head>
         <p>The Yale Bookplate Collection was formerly housed in Sterling Memorial Library. The collection was incorporated into the Arts of the Book Collection in 1984 and then moved to the Seeley G. Mudd Library in 1990. In 2011, it was transferred to the Robert B. Haas Family Arts Library.</p>  
      </acqinfo>
      <accessrestrict id="aspace_8baf296159d6108da8c67ca573069012">
         <head>Conditions Governing Access</head>
         <p>The materials are open for research.</p>  
      </accessrestrict>
      <userestrict id="aspace_2c7c8a1f60d7e48bd32b0bd83644e3ae">
         <head>Conditions Governing Use</head>
         <p>Copyright has not been transferred to Yale University.</p>  
      </userestrict>
      <prefercite id="aspace_fc1a7f7283ee5da57dad226a09ed4daf">
         <head>Preferred Citation</head>
         <p>Collection of Bookplates by Timothy Cole, Robert B. Haas Family Arts Library, Yale University.</p>  
      </prefercite>
      <processinfo id="aspace_f1d473cb570a1068ce96e9cb54bc302c">
         <head>Processing Information</head>
         <p>The collection was removed from filing cabinets which housed bookplates by individual artists. Some materials included in this collection indicate the provenance of the following bookplate collectors or collections: Edith M. Baker, Frank S. Hatch, William Fowler and Ada M. Hopson, and Irene D. Andrews Pace.</p>  
      </processinfo>
      <bioghist id="aspace_9db39a1dbe8bcdbe7694c85988a16d55">
         <head>Biographical / Historical</head>
         <p>Timothy Cole (1852-1931) was an American wood engraver. In addition to designing bookplates, Cole had a long career working in magazine illustration, notably with <title localtype="simple" render="italic">
               <part>The Century</part>
            </title>, and creating printed reproductions of European paintings.</p>  
      </bioghist>
      <scopecontent id="aspace_2f528bbefb7094fe3c57de2a4eecc98e">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>The collection includes bookplates designed by Timothy Cole for both individual and institutional patrons.</p>  
      </scopecontent>
      <arrangement id="aspace_b67cb43cef0bdc8b7b86c92a5dd6dd69">
         <head>Arrangement</head>
         <p>Organized into three series: I. Bookplates – Individuals, 1915-1930. II. Bookplates – Institutions, 1908-1926. III. Ephemera, undated.</p>  
      </arrangement>
